
Overview of noun hostile

The noun hostile has 1 sense (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. hostile -- (troops belonging to the enemy's military forces; "the platoon ran into a pack of hostiles")

Overview of adj hostile

The adj hostile has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (5) hostile -- (characterized by enmity or ill will; "a hostile nation"; "a hostile remark"; "hostile actions")
2. (3) hostile -- (not belonging to your own country's forces or those of an ally; "hostile naval and air forces")
3. hostile -- (impossible to bring into friendly accord; "hostile factions")
4. hostile, uncongenial, unfriendly -- (very unfavorable to life or growth; "a hostile climate"; "an uncongenial atmosphere"; "an uncongenial soil"; "the unfriendly environment at high altitudes")
5. hostile -- (unsolicited and resisted by the management of the target company ( used of attempts to buy or take control of a business); "hostile takeover"; "hostile tender offer"; "hostile bid")
